title: ACC's medical observers another set of eyes to spot injury
text: > North Carolina ACC's medical observers another set of eyes to spot injury FILE - In this Nov. 22, 2014, file photo, Florida State medical staff escorts injured Florida State wide receiver Rashad Greene in the first half of an NCAA college football game against Boston College in Tallahassee, Fla. ACC Commissioner John Swofford embraced an NCAA proposal and implemented a league-wide policy that ACC teams would be required to assign a medical observer selected by each respective school for every game _ home, away, and at neutral sites. (AP Photo/Mark Wallheiser, File)
